The revised allocation from the Maharashtra Power Development Agency was increased to Rs. 39.9463 crore. Out of the revised provision, funds amounting to Rs. 38.3060 crore have been disbursed and the remaining allocation has been returned.

However, the revised allocation from the Finance Department was reduced to Rs. 594.00 crore. Hence, the funds have been disbursed as per the revised provision.
